<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Elessara on 05-30-2000 02:00 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">FYI Alli ....

I've had EM boots for months.  Hell I had two pairs for awhile.  Never wore them.  Simply could not give up the 9 wis on the efreeti boots.  Had a prismatic shield for awhile too.  Didn't use that hardly at all.  Got a bracer that hung around for a bit.  Didn't wear that either.  I got real lucky one night in Hate and got arms AND legs ... well, the legs took care of the 9 wis problem on the efreeti boots, so I switched to purple legs, feet and arms ... didn't want to lose the 5 wis on a bracer though, so still didn't wear the 1 bracer I had.  Got another bracer ... didn't wear it.  Ahh, got my BP, well that takes care of the 10 wis from the bracers so, off came the reverents.  All I need are gloves which I will wear regardless of AC loss ... I need the dex lol.  And I look just silly with gold hands and purple the rest of me.

/shrug

Don't worry about wearing the EM for now until you want to.  When I didn't enter a random, people just asked why I didn't and I said I already had.  No one gave me any trouble over it, so I wouldn't worry.  People will remember your name more than your armor.

Oh, and about only saying you want in on the legs/bp etc.  On Tunare, BP is seniority usually - at least on most raids - or its last two items are automatically granted.  If more than one person needs an item as last two, they roll for it.  If seniority cannot be established, then all who need roll for it.

Elessara Ard'Hielle
Cleric of Tunare
Tunare server

[This message has been edited by Elessara (edited 05-30-2000).]</TEXTAREA>
